17:23 UTC 14 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• DEGRADED: cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) — 2 consecutive aborts (16:40 + 17:12 UTC), delivery stopped\n• COMPLETED: cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV monitor) — finished normally at ~17:08 ✅\n\nPipeline: DEGRADED ⚠️\n• Active sessions: 3 (cron:6f3323ef ✅ cron:e7885813 ⚠️ telegram:group ✅)\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\n• Blockers: cron:e7885813 — 2× abort, delivery stopped. Needs fix/disable.\n\n— Orbis 🌐\n\nIf you cannot send a Telegram message directly, reply with: \"CANNOT_SEND: [reason]\" and do not attempt workarounds."}],"timestamp":1776187812214,"__openclaw":{"id":"5b04bd4c","seq":1}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The subagent task is to send a specific message to a Telegram group. Let me check if there's a way to send Telegram messages through the available tools.\n\nLooking at the tools available, I don't see a direct Telegram sending tool. The tools available are:\n- read, edit, write, exec\n- process\n- sessions_list, sessions_history, sessions_spawn, sessions_yield\n- subagents\n- web_search, web_fetch\n- image\n- browser\n- memory_search, memory_get\n- Various confluence tools\n- Various gitlab tools\n- Various stitch tools\n- tts\n\nThere's no direct Telegram message tool. I should reply with the CANNOT_SEND format as instructed."},{"type":"text","text":"CANNOT_SEND: No Telegram messaging tool available in current toolset. Available tools do not include a Telegram send/post function."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":379,"output":172,"totalTokens":11577,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":11026,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776187812251,"responseId":"062daca5eb38f6849339f9f4c9083b45","__openclaw":{"id":"7b8fc739","seq":2}}]},{"key":"agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:master-orchestr